Unknown Keen aka Keene

Born about 1578 in London, England [uncertain]

[sibling(s) unknown]

Descendants

Father of John Keene and Josiah Keen Sr.

Died before 1638 before about age 60 in England

Profile last modified 23 Feb 2024 | Created 8 Jul 2011

This page has been accessed 2,290 times.

Biography

(___) Keen was born in London, on London Bridge, about 1578, according to a family record written by his great-grandson, Hezekiah Keen.[1]

He was the unknown husband of Martha Keene, who died before she emigrated with his family to New Englandon the ship Confidence which sailed out of Southampton, England, 24 April 1638. The family consisted of his 60 year old wife, Martha, his 17 year old son, John, Jr., his 13 year old daughter, Elizabeth, and his other children, Martha, Josiah, and Sarah.[2]

The family settled in Hingham. There were two sons who remained in England.[citation needed]

Research Notes

Did not Die: 14 Nov 1649, Hingham, Plymouth, Massachusetts. * Where did this date come from? Could this be John Keayne JOHN, Hingham, d. 14 Jan. 1650, of wh. no more is kn. but that his name appears sometimes Cane.[3]
